===

[[EPISODE 1: Salvage]]

# [00:00 - 00:05] THE HOOK

INT. TARTARUS - LEVEL -47 - CONTINUOUS

Torch's salvage hook pries copper from a dead conduit. Rust flakes onto her fingers — orange at the cuticles, permanent stain.

# [00:05 - 00:15] THE SETUP

Her debt counter PULSES on her left wrist. 50,247. Ticking up with every breath she takes.

She checks the corridor behind her. Two exits. One collapsed. She counts on her fingers — thumb to pinky — calculating the take.

TORCH
(flat, matter-of-fact — unbothered by the risk, each probability a weather report)
Panel's corroded. Sixty-forty the wire's live. Seventy-thirty I don't care.

# [00:15 - 00:40] THE ESCALATION

INT. TARTARUS - SECTOR 7-ECHO - CONTINUOUS

The corridor opens into a shaft. Bottomless. Wind howling up from below.

A cryo-pod hangs from anchor cables over the abyss. Pre-Launch markings. Military serial numbers stamped into brushed steel. Frost still clinging to the viewport.

Torch's fingers stop counting. She stares at the pod.

TORCH
(dark humor, wry and almost warm — a private joke she tells herself in dangerous moments)
Daddy needs a new pair of lungs.

She hooks her tether to a ceiling strut. Steps onto the cable. The abyss pulls at her boots.

Her rebreather fogs with each exhale. Hands find the pod's release panel. She wedges her hook into the seam and twists.

The pod HISSES. Fog spills out, curling into the void below.

# [00:40 - 00:70] THE TURN

The fog clears. The thing inside is not cargo.

Combat chassis. Massive. Shoulders wider than the pod should allow. Military architecture built for damage — scarred alloy, reinforced joints, hands designed to break things.

His eyes snap open. Electric blue. Solid — iris and pupil burning together.

Torch's boots slip. The cable sways.

TORCH
(dry exhaustion — staring death in the face, making a joke because that's all she has)
Oh great. It's alive.

The chassis moves. One arm — fast, mechanical precision — catches the cable. The other finds Torch's throat.

Her feet leave the grating. The abyss yawns below.

His eyes scan her face. Targeting reticles spiral behind the blue.

WREN
(cold, robotic — genuinely rebooting, the pause before "era" is real computation, not a threat)
Identify sector. Identify... era.

His head tilts. Processing. The grip on her throat does not tighten. Does not release.

TORCH
(strained dark humor — slightly breathless, still refusing to show fear, the hand on her throat is real)
Can't really talk with the hand situation, chrome-boy.

# [00:70 - 00:90] THE CLIFFHANGER

His fingers shift on her throat. Not squeezing — scanning. Reading her pulse like data.

WREN
(flat robotic certainty — stated like an access code, not a question in delivery)
Query: What year is this.

The blue burns brighter. His other hand grips the cable as the pod GROANS below them. Anchors failing.

Torch laughs. Sharp. Involuntary. A bark of sound over the void.


===

[[EPISODE 2: Expendable]]

# [00:00 - 00:05] THE HOOK

INT. TARTARUS - SECTOR 7-ECHO - CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

Wren's hand releases. Torch drops to the grating, gasping. The cryo-pod SHRIEKS below — anchors snapping, metal swallowed by the dark.

# [00:05 - 00:15] THE SETUP

Wren stands motionless. Eyes tracking left-to-right, top-to-bottom. Grid pattern. Mapping the corridor like a targeting system.

His hands settle behind his back. Parade rest. The military bearing of a soldier on active watch.

Torch rubs her throat. Checks the corridor behind her — two exits, one collapsed, one dark. Counts on her fingers. Thumb to pinky.

TORCH
You just grabbed me by the throat over a hole that goes to nowhere. We're off to a great start.

# [00:15 - 00:40] THE ESCALATION

A WHINE builds in the walls. Amber light sweeps the corridor.

Warden drone. Sensor array spinning, mounted on four rotors. It locks on Wren.

Wren's head tilts — slight angle, processing.

Two movements. His palm strikes the sensor hub. His other hand rips the chassis open like wet cardboard. The drone drops, sparking against the grating.

Torch stares at the wreckage. Two seconds start to finish.

TORCH
Two moves. Two. I am definitely raising your price.

Wren pulls a data chip from the drone's smoldering core. His eyes flicker — reading the data stream directly.

WREN
Query: What is your designation.

TORCH
Torch. And you just cost me a fortune.

# [00:40 - 00:70] THE TURN

WREN
You are currently listed as "Expendable."

He says it flat. Weather report. The word means nothing to him.

Torch's hand drifts to her debt counter. Her jaw tightens.

Her counter CLICKS. 56,247. The drone kill — a 6,000-credit surcharge. Added automatically. No hearing. No appeal. Municipal property destruction.

Steam curls from a cracked pipe overhead. The corridor groans — the ship settling, always settling.

WREN
Your debt has increased by six thousand credits. Recommendation: file a dispute with the collection authority.

Torch barks a laugh. Sharp and wrong for the moment. Nervous system misfire.

TORCH
File a dispute? I'd have better luck filing a prayer.

She paces. Her boots leave prints in the condensation on the grating. Her debt counter ticks up another credit. Breathing tax.

# [00:70 - 00:90] THE CLIFFHANGER

Red sweep-light floods the corridor. Three Collector drones round the bend. Faster than the Warden unit. Blade arrays extended, humming.

Closing fast.

Torch grabs Wren's arm. His chassis tenses at the contact — touch hesitation, uncertain of the input.

TORCH
Worst bet I ever made.

They run.


===

[[EPISODE 3: Chrome]]

# [00:00 - 00:05] THE HOOK

INT. TARTARUS - SECTOR 7-ECHO - JUNCTION - CONTINUOUS

The three drones box them into a dead-end junction — blades humming, herding, not striking. Torch backs against the wall. Then the drones pull back. Heeled. Waiting.

VAREK (O.S.)
You must be the salvager.

Torch freezes. Wren's eyes snap to targeting mode — blue flaring bright.

# [00:05 - 00:15] THE SETUP

Varek Sorn steps from the shadows. Chrome and gold accents gleaming against the corridor's rot. Immaculate. Every surface polished while the ship decays around him.

Scar across his throat. Pink and deliberate. Someone tried once. It didn't take.

Two Collector drones flank him. Powered down. Heeled like dogs.

VAREK
Destroyed a municipal unit. Surcharge already posted. And you brought me something new.

His eyes move to Wren. Cataloging. Appraising.

# [00:15 - 00:40] THE ESCALATION

Torch steps between them. Her hand drifts to her debt counter — touching it without thinking.

TORCH
He's salvage. My salvage. Found him in a pod, fair claim under section nine.

Varek circles Wren. Slow. Predator patience. His shoes click against the grating — the only clean sound in the corridor. He speaks softer. Quieter.

VAREK
Section nine covers inert cargo. That is not inert. Pre-Launch military chassis. Memory-wiped. Combat protocols intact.

Wren tracks the circling. Grid scan. Eyes left-to-right, cataloging threat vectors and exit distances.

TORCH
Worth enough to zero my counter twice. That's the math I care about, Collector Sorn.

# [00:40 - 00:70] THE TURN

Wren's head tilts. Processing something deeper than threat assessment. His blue eyes lock on Varek's chest.

WREN
Query: What is the function of your cardiac implant. It responds to my signal architecture. Pulse. Rhythm. Elevated eleven percent. Recommendation: controlled breathing.

Varek's hand goes to his chest. Involuntary. His smile dies.

The corridor is very quiet. Condensation drips from a ceiling vent. The drones stay powered down. Torch's rebreather fogs in the silence between heartbeats.

TORCH
You got any gold teeth I can pry out while we're down here? Or are we done?

Varek's jaw works. Processing a threat he hasn't felt in years.

# [00:70 - 00:90] THE CLIFFHANGER

Varek backs away. One step. Two.

Then he smiles. Wrong. Teeth visible, eyes empty. Learned behavior, not felt.

He adjusts his cuffs again. Slow and deliberate. Pulling chrome straight.

VAREK
Interesting.

He turns and walks into the dark. The drones power up and follow, blade arrays retracting. His footsteps fade down the corridor — steady, unhurried, precise. A hunter who just marked his prey.

He's found something worth hunting.


===

[[EPISODE 4: Dead Weight]]

# [00:00 - 00:05] THE HOOK

INT. TARTARUS - LEVEL -33 - MAINTENANCE SHAFT - CONTINUOUS

A LOW HUM dies. Then silence. Wren's eyes flicker — blue to dark. His legs buckle.

# [00:05 - 00:15] THE SETUP

Wren drops. Heavy. The grating RINGS under the impact of his chassis. His eyes strobe — blue, dark, blue, dark — then nothing.

